benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/phase - Retrieve phase for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request coverage: 200 OK responses with correct Phase data for valid inputs (TC01, TC02, TC15, TC16, TC13).
Query Parameters coverage: Tests cover various parameter combinations, including missing parameters and extra parameters (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC14).
Authorization coverage: Unauthorized access scenario (TC09) produces 401 with proper error messaging.
Error handling coverage: Scenarios for non-existent subscriptions (TC05), invalid input formats (TC06/TC07), out-of-range dates (TC08), and system failure (TC10).
Security coverage: SQL injection test (TC11) validates input sanitization and avoids leakage of internal errors.
Performance coverage: Large dataset (TC13) and concurrent requests (TC16) demonstrate performance characteristics.
Edge-case handling: Empty database (TC12) returns 404 with appropriate message.
gaps: Pagination: No tests covering pagination behavior for large datasets or page navigation.
Rate Limiting: No tests to verify throttling or 429 responses under burst traffic.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or 304 Not Modified handling.
403 Forbidden: Only 401 Unauthorized tested; no tests for 403 when authenticated user lacks permissions.
Empty Response body: No test returning 200 with an empty body when there are no phases for the given date (instead of 404).
Time zone and date-format edge cases: No tests for time-zone variations beyond the tested formats.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify handling of page and limit parameters when the dataset is large.
Add rate limiting tests to ensure 429 responses under burst traffic.
Add caching tests to verify ETag and Cache-Control headers and 304 Not Modified responses.
Add 403 Forbidden scenarios where authenticated user lacks the required permissions.
Add tests for empty-response scenarios with 200 and empty body or 204, depending on API design, to confirm correct behavior when no data is available.
Add tests for time zone variations and edge-case date formats beyond the current invalid-date tests.
